 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.41","title":"[audit][trace] Make ReplayCheckpoint creation deterministic for identical trace positions","description":"ReplayCheckpoint::new currently stamps created_at from SystemTime::now(), so taking the same checkpoint twice against the same trace position yields different serialized checkpoint bytes and leaks ambient wall clock back into the deterministic replay toolchain. Patch src/trace/streaming.rs so checkpoint creation is deterministic for a given trace metadata + events_processed pair, add focused regression coverage for identical-position stability and monotonic differentiation across positions, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T03:06:17.083408797Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T03:13:10.603716194Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T03:13:10.603691518Z","close_reason":"ReplayCheckpoint no longer uses ambient wall clock; identical-position checkpoint serialization is deterministic and targeted replay checkpoint tests passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","streaming","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.41","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T03:06:17.083408797Z","created_by":"PinkForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.42","title":"[audit][web] Give circuit-breaker and rate-limit middleware deterministic time getters","description":"src/web/middleware.rs hard-codes SystemTime::now() inside CircuitBreakerMiddleware::call() and RateLimitMiddleware::call(), so the web wrapper layer bypasses the runtime's explicit time discipline and cannot be driven deterministically in tests the way the service-layer equivalents can. Patch the middleware wrappers to carry an injectable time_getter with wall-clock defaults, route both combinators through it, add focused regression coverage proving deterministic open-window / retry-after behavior under a synthetic clock, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-09T03:15:07.733796768Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T03:21:53.114671607Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T03:21:53.114646020Z","close_reason":"web circuit-breaker and rate-limit middleware now use injectable time getters; deterministic middleware clock regressions passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","time","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.42","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T03:15:07.733796768Z","created_by":"PinkForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.43","title":"[audit][service] Prevent Retry::poll_ready from stranding inner readiness reservations","description":"Retry currently delegates poll_ready() to self.inner but call() executes against self.inner.clone() inside RetryFuture. For stateful-ready wrappers like ConcurrencyLimit, outer poll_ready can reserve readiness/permits on the original inner while the actual request path waits on a clone, stranding capacity and potentially deadlocking the request. Fix src/service/retry.rs so outer poll_ready does not mutate or strand readiness state on the source inner, add focused regression coverage proving a retry-wrapped ConcurrencyLimit call no longer deadlocks after poll_ready, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WindyOtter","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T05:00:40.363575157Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T05:08:06.083667219Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T05:08:06.083642894Z","close_reason":"Patched Retry::poll_ready to avoid stranding inner readiness reservations; added regression coverage. rch cargo check --all-targets passed, while cargo test/clippy/fmt hit unrelated repo-frontier failures.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","retry","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.43","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:00:40.363575157Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}

